cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on following navigation instructions on a quadcopter simulator using neural networks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses imitation learning to train the model. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the model incorporates a pinhole camera projection model within the network to build an explicit semantic map. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses a fully-differentiable neural network architecture and a modified variant of DAgger for training. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with real-time control of a quadcopter.
